Rome Takes Special Anti-Pollution Measures
ROME , December 23 ( Xinhua ) -- All buses and subways in Rome offered free services on Tuesday and Wednesday to alleviate pollution in the city by reducing the use of private cars during the Christmas season .
Traffic jams and pollution usually get worse at Christmas time with more people using cars for shopping and holiday-making .
Other Italian cities have also taken similar measures to reduce pollution .
Pollution levels in major Italian cities such as Rome , Florence and Turin remained very high -- some reportedly higher than international standards .
